A Studio Ghibli style illustration of two 10-year-old twin boys with wide curious eyes kneeling on a wooden floor, surrounded by scattered electronic components, circuit boards, colorful wires, and tiny mechanical parts from an unboxed robot kit. A gentle afternoon light streams through a window, casting warm golden rays across the scene. In the background, a kindly elderly man with weathered hands holds a soldering iron, ready to teach. The atmosphere is one of wonder and anticipation, with the promise of creation hanging in the air. Soft, painterly textures and warm earthy tones evoke nostalgia and the magic of childhood discovery.
